eNCA's Rofhiwa Madzena has the details. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - The owners of the Domino's Pizza franchise in South Africa will be auctioning off its assets which include fifty stores. The company was liquidated, causing over 700 employees to lose their jobs. READ: SA Lockdown: Restaurants protest restrictions The decision to auction off the franchise was made after Taste Holdings failed to acquire an investor for the ailing business. Owner and JSE-listed Taste Holdings, announced last year that it would be exiting the food business by getting rid of Starbucks, Domino's Pizza, Maxi's, and The Fish & Chip Co. to shift its focus to luxury goods. READ: Curfew, alcohol sale ban a blow to restaurants Domino's Pizza joins a list of several restaurants that have faced closure because of the tough economic environment before and during the lockdown.